<seg id=1> The National Youth League will make the biggest strip of cloth in the world to support the national leaders. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Singapore The National Youth League will make the biggest strip of cloth in the world to show their love and support to their country and their leaders. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Youth League will hold a meeting on the 24th of this month, and their letter on behalf of the nation will be handed over to Prime Minister Go Chok Tong. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In the meeting, the Youth League will present the Patriotic Strips of Cloth, and one of them may be brought into the Guinness Book of Records. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The area of the cloth was 150m x 100m. The Youth League in Choa Chu Kang maked it; they applied to bring it into the Guinness Book of Records. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Youth League expressed that the activities were made to show their love and support to their leaders. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> "We want all to know that when some want to overthrow the democratic government with non-democratic and unlawful ways, all our people will never be worldly wise and play safe or keep silent." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Meanwhile, the Youth League expressed that neither foreigners, foreign governments or leaders nor media should try to intervene in the internal affairs of Singapore. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> "Although we trust our government's ability to deal with any matter harming the national security, some irresponsible activities have challenged our patience. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Therefore, the Youth League called on all the people to resist external temptation to affect the national security. </seg>
</p>
